<TITLE> Four policemen suspended for slack duty on Dulu assignment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, June 13 (bdnews24.com)  Four policemen were suspended Wednesday for letting detained BNP leader Ruhul Kuddus Talukder Dulu spend time with party activists on his way to Rajshahi from Dhaka Central Jail, a senior police officer said. Suspended policemen are Ashraful Haq, Milon Miah, Noor Alom Miah and Mamunur Rashid. Additional Superintendent of Police for Rajshahi Nazmul Ahmed confirmed the temporary suspension order. Another police officer preferring anonymity told bdnews24.com that Dulu, former deputy minister for land, was being taken to Rajshahi Monday night to produce him before court. The prison van, which carried Dulu to Rajshahi, had stopovers at his Natore home, Gurpatti and West Bypass where some BNP leaders and activists were waiting. Dulu also talked to some people by cellphone in connivance with the policemen assigned to escort him to Rajshahi. The suspension order came from the office of the superintendent of police, Ahmed said. bdnews24.c
